title: Bluegamba's Choice No. 14
description:
Here&#039;s another eclectic choice from the man who doesn&#039;t know what to like and therefore likes all instead!

Raheem DeVaughn&#039;s album is very well crafted. I just couldn&#039;t choose between these two songs.
The Fleshtones album is a must buy! They sound refreshing even though their sound sometimes remind me of the beginning Beatles.
"What Made Milwaukee Famous" keeps astounding me. Their new album is coming out in March. I&#039;m looking forward to that. If only I could ever get used to their horrible name....
Shelby Lynne has made a tribute album to Dusty Springfield. I never thought I could like something like that, but once I started listening to this album I caught myself humming along and singing along. Reason enough to include a song in this choice.
The Drive-by Truckers are swerving between Tom Petty, Neil Young and Lambchop. Their albums are always of high quality.
"Atlas Sound" has made an album that makes you dream. A thought-full collection of sounds.
The Evangelicals have received praise enough. 
Adele is the new hit from England. Saw her on Jools Holland and loved her immediately.
The songs from High Places are not new, but have been "gathered" for the first time. They make a great collection.

01 Raheem DeVaughn - Butterflies
02 Yoav - Club Thing (LaCrate Mix)
03 Raheem DeVaughn - Friday (Shut The Club Down)
04 Eli "Paperboy" Reed and the True Loves - Am I Wasting My Time
05 What Made Milwaukee Famous - Trying To Never Catch Up
06 What Made Milwaukee Famous - Short On Shields
07 Sheryl Crow - Now That You&#039;re Gone
08 Shelby Lynne - Willie And Laura Mae Jones
09 Drive-by Truckers - You And Your Crystal Meth
10 Adele - Daydreamer
11 The Whigs - Sleep Sunshine
12 The Bird And The Bee - Birthday
13 Colour Revolt - Naked And Red
14 Drive-by Truckers - The Man I Shot
15 The Fleshtones - First Date (Are You Coming On To Me?)
16 The Fleshtones - Love Yourself
17 American Music Club - San Francisco
18 State Bird - The Golden Glowing Mask
19 The Heavenly States - The Race
20 Evangelicals - Skeleton Man
21 Atlas Sound - Cold As Ice
22 High Places - Sandy Feat (7" version)

Have fun again! Don&#039;t forget to check out mr. Shankly&#039;s Love Child.
Hope to hear from you soon.
